      <p>The committee was appointed on 17 Feb. (<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s Additional Committee Assignments, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-05-02-0033" class="document">2 Jan.  6 Nov.</a>, above).</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d073n2-ptr" id="PJA05d073n2">2</a>
      <p>Now Portland, Maine.</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d073n3-ptr" id="PJA05d073n3">3</a>
      <p>Probably John Noble (<span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Laws of New Hampshire</span>, 10 vols., 19041922, 4:610).</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d073n4-ptr" id="PJA05d073n4">4</a>
      <p>Joseph Barnard (William Willis, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">The History of Portland</span>, 2d edn., Portland, Maine, 1865, facsim. edn., 1972, p. 585).</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d073n5-ptr" id="PJA05d073n5">5</a>
      <p>Ebenezer Hazard (17441817), appointed in late 1776 as a surveyor general of the Continental post office, later became postmaster general (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Allen Johnson and Dumas Malone, eds., &lt;i&gt;Dictionary of American Biography&lt;/i&gt;, New York, 19281936; 20 vols. plus index and supplements. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">DAB</span></span>).</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d073n6-ptr" id="PJA05d073n6">6</a>
      <p>Probably Jeremiah Libbey (<span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">New Hampshire State Papers Series</span>, ed. Nathaniel Bouton and others, 40 vols., Concord, N.H., 18671943, 13:286, 294, 295, 297, 301).</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d073n7-ptr" id="PJA05d073n7">7</a>
      <p>Jonathan Hastings Jr.s memorial was read on 19 March (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Worthington C. Ford and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Continental Congress, 17741789&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 19041937; 34 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">JCC</span></span>, 7:184).</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d073n8-ptr" id="PJA05d073n8">8</a>
      <p>Freeman was one of Falmouths members in the House of Representatives (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Journals of the House of Representatives of Massachusetts&lt;/i&gt; [[1715-]], Boston, reprinted by the Massachusetts Historical Society, 1919-. (For the years for which reprints are not yet available, the original printings are cited, by year and session.) ]">Mass., <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">House Jour.</span></span>, 17761777, 1st sess., p. 5).</p>
